msgstr "\"\""

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:151
msgid "# 1. prefer the env var (never blocks)\n"
msgstr "# 1. préférer la variable d'env (ne bloque jamais)\n"

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:152
msgid "# 2. fall back to stdin if it's piped in\n"
msgstr "# 2. se replier sur stdin s'il est passé en pipe\n"

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:154
msgid "# 3. nothing at all → minimal context\n"
msgstr "# 3. rien du tout → contexte minimal\n"

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:157
msgid "# 4. parse the JSON\n"
msgstr "# 4. parser le JSON\n"

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:159
msgid "# 5. malformed → degrade gracefully\n"
msgstr "# 5. mal formé → dégradation gracieuse\n"

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:163
msgid ""
"Once you have `ctx`, everything else is ordinary shell work: "
"`ctx[\"repos\"]` gives you each repo's on-disk `path`, and `git diff` / `git "
"commit` are just subprocess calls into that path."
msgstr ""
"Une fois que tu as `ctx`, tout le reste n'est que du travail shell "
"ordinaire : `ctx[\"repos\"]` te donne le `path` sur disque de chaque dépôt, "
"et `git diff` / `git commit` ne sont que des appels de sous-processus dans "
"ce chemin."

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:167
msgid "3. The three output shapes a plugin can print"
msgstr "3. Les trois formes de sortie qu'un plugin peut imprimer"

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:169
msgid ""
"A plugin can print three different kinds of output, depending on how it's "
"called. You don't have to support all three, but a good one does:"
msgstr ""
"Un plugin peut imprimer trois types de sortie différents, selon la façon "
"dont il est appelé. Tu n'es pas obligé de tous les prendre en charge, mais "
"un bon plugin le fait :"

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:172
msgid ""
"**Plain text** — the default. When someone runs `haw commit-ai` in a "
"terminal, print friendly human-readable text."
msgstr ""
"**Texte brut** — le comportement par défaut. Quand quelqu'un lance `haw "
"commit-ai` dans un terminal, imprime un texte convivial et lisible par un "
"humain."

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:174
msgid ""
"**A machine report** — when called with `--format json`, print a "
"**`haw.plugin.report/1`** document: `{schema, plugin, ok, summary, findings}"
"`. Tools and CI parse this instead of scraping human text."
msgstr ""
"**Un rapport machine** — appelé avec `--format json`, imprime un document "
"**`haw.plugin.report/1`** : `{schema, plugin, ok, summary, findings}`. Les "
"outils et la CI parsent ça au lieu de gratter du texte humain."

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:177
msgid ""
"**A cockpit panel** — when haw wants to render your plugin inside the TUI "
"cockpit, it sets the environment variable `HAW_RENDER=1` and puts "
"`\"intent\": \"render\"` in the context. Your plugin then prints a "
"**`haw.plugin.view/1`** document: `{schema, title, lines[]}`. haw draws "
"those lines in the cockpit's Plugins view (press `7`)."
msgstr ""
"**Un panneau de cockpit** — quand haw veut afficher ton plugin dans le "
"cockpit TUI, il définit la variable d'environnement `HAW_RENDER=1` et place "
"`\"intent\": \"render\"` dans le contexte. Ton plugin imprime alors un "
"document **`haw.plugin.view/1`** : `{schema, title, lines[]}`. haw dessine "
"ces lignes dans la vue Plugins du cockpit (appuie sur `7`)."

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:183
msgid ""
"The three JSON schemas live in [`schemas/`](https://github.com/Nastwinns/"
"hawser/tree/main/schemas) — they're the source of truth for every field."
msgstr ""
"Les trois schémas JSON vivent dans [`schemas/`](https://github.com/Nastwinns/"
"hawser/tree/main/schemas) — ce sont la source de vérité pour chaque champ."

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:187
msgid "4. Scaffold the plugin"
msgstr "4. Générer le squelette du plugin"

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:189
msgid ""
"You don't have to write any of this from a blank file. haw generates a "
"runnable skeleton that already implements the contract for you."
msgstr ""
"Tu n'as pas à écrire tout ça depuis un fichier vide. haw génère un squelette "
"exécutable qui implémente déjà le contrat pour toi."

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:192
msgid "**Prerequisite:** you need Python 3 installed. Check it:"
msgstr "**Prérequis :** tu as besoin de Python 3 installé. Vérifie-le :"

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:195
msgid "# any recent Python 3.x is fine\n"
msgstr "# n'importe quel Python 3.x récent convient\n"

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:198
msgid "Now scaffold:"
msgstr "Génère maintenant le squelette :"

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:204
msgid ""
"```console\n"
"created ./haw-commit-ai/haw-commit-ai   (executable, python3)\n"
"created ./haw-commit-ai/README.md\n"
"next:\n"
"  chmod is already set — drop it on PATH:\n"
"    PATH=\"$PWD/haw-commit-ai:$PATH\" haw commit-ai\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```console\n"
"created ./haw-commit-ai/haw-commit-ai   (executable, python3)\n"
"created ./haw-commit-ai/README.md\n"
"next:\n"
"  chmod is already set — drop it on PATH:\n"
"    PATH=\"$PWD/haw-commit-ai:$PATH\" haw commit-ai\n"
"```"

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:212
msgid "Two files land in a new `./haw-commit-ai/` directory:"
msgstr ""
"Deux fichiers apparaissent dans un nouveau répertoire `./haw-commit-ai/` :"

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:214
msgid ""
"**`haw-commit-ai`** — the plugin executable itself (a Python script with a "
"`#!/usr/bin/env python3` shebang, already marked executable)."
msgstr ""
"**`haw-commit-ai`** — l'exécutable du plugin lui-même (un script Python avec "
"un shebang `#!/usr/bin/env python3`, déjà marqué exécutable)."

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:216
msgid "**`README.md`** — notes for the plugin."
msgstr "**`README.md`** — des notes pour le plugin."

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:218
msgid ""
"The scaffold already reads `$HAW_JSON`, handles `--help` and `--format "
"json`, and emits a `haw.plugin.report/1`. It's a correct, working plugin as-"
"is. In the next sections we'll replace its body with our MCP-capable version."
msgstr ""
"Le squelette lit déjà `$HAW_JSON`, gère `--help` et `--format json`, et émet "
"un `haw.plugin.report/1`. C'est un plugin correct et fonctionnel tel quel. "
"Dans les sections suivantes, on remplacera son corps par notre version "
"capable de MCP."

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:224
msgid ""
"**Why Python?** Because the MCP SDK we'll use for the Claude side is Python-"
"first. The plugin _face_ stays zero-dependency (standard library only); only "
"the `--mcp` face needs one extra package, which we install later with `pip "
"install mcp`."
msgstr ""
"**Pourquoi Python ?** Parce que le SDK MCP qu'on utilisera côté Claude est "
"pensé d'abord pour Python. Le _visage_ plugin reste sans dépendance "
"(bibliothèque standard uniquement) ; seul le visage `--mcp` a besoin d'un "
"paquet supplémentaire, qu'on installera plus tard avec `pip install mcp`."

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:230
msgid "5. The plugin faces: human text, JSON report, and cockpit panel"
msgstr ""
"5. Les visages du plugin : texte humain, rapport JSON et panneau de cockpit"

