#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:394
msgid ""
"**`haw_context()`** — hands Claude the workspace shape: root, stack, and "
"repos. This is how Claude learns your fleet exists."
msgstr ""
"**`haw_context()`** — tend à Claude la forme de l'espace de travail : root, "
"stack et dépôts. C'est ainsi que Claude apprend que ta flotte existe."

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:396
msgid ""
"**`repo_diff(repo)`** — returns one repo's diff so Claude reads exactly what "
"changed before writing about it."
msgstr ""
"**`repo_diff(repo)`** — renvoie le diff d'un dépôt pour que Claude lise "
"exactement ce qui a changé avant d'écrire à ce sujet."

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:398
msgid ""
"**`changeset_repos_tool()`** — tells Claude which repos are in play right "
"now."
msgstr ""
"**`changeset_repos_tool()`** — indique à Claude quels dépôts sont en jeu en "
"ce moment."

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:399
msgid ""
"**`write_commit(repo, message)`** — actually commits, but only inside the "
"workspace root (the path-guard refuses anything outside)."
msgstr ""
"**`write_commit(repo, message)`** — committe réellement, mais uniquement à "
"l'intérieur de la racine de l'espace de travail (le garde-chemin refuse tout "
"ce qui est en dehors)."

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:401
msgid ""
"**`draft_pr(repo, title, body)`** — returns PR text; **dry by default**, so "
"it never pushes anything unless you explicitly pass `submit=True`."
msgstr ""
"**`draft_pr(repo, title, body)`** — renvoie le texte de la PR ; **à blanc "
"par défaut**, donc il ne pousse jamais rien sauf si tu passes explicitement "
"`submit=True`."

