msgid "# haw-commit-ai should be listed\n"
msgstr "# haw-commit-ai devrait apparaître dans la liste\n"

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:506
msgid ""
"Inside a Claude session, `/mcp` shows the connected server and its tools. At "
"Level 1 that's `haw_context`, `repo_diff`, `changeset_repos_tool`, "
"`write_commit`, and `draft_pr`. Once you add Level 2 below, `changeset_diff` "
"and `draft_changeset_pr` join them."
msgstr ""
"Dans une session Claude, `/mcp` affiche le serveur connecté et ses outils. "
"Au Niveau 1, ce sont `haw_context`, `repo_diff`, `changeset_repos_tool`, "
"`write_commit` et `draft_pr`. Une fois que tu ajoutes le Niveau 2 ci-"
"dessous, `changeset_diff` et `draft_changeset_pr` les rejoignent."

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:510
msgid "10. Worked example — Claude writes your commit and PR text"
msgstr "10. Exemple concret — Claude écrit ton texte de commit et de PR"

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:512
msgid ""
"Make a change across two repos in your workspace (say `kernel` and `hal`), "
"stage them, then ask Claude — from inside the workspace directory:"
msgstr ""
"Fais un changement sur deux dépôts de ton espace de travail (disons `kernel` "
"et `hal`), indexe-les, puis demande à Claude — depuis le répertoire de "
"l'espace de travail :"

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:515
msgid ""
"_\"Read the diffs for the repos touched by my current changeset and write a "
"conventional-commit message for each. Then draft a single cross-repo PR "
"body. Commit each repo with its message; leave the PR as a dry draft.\"_"
msgstr ""
"_« Lis les diffs des dépôts touchés par mon changeset courant et écris un "
"message de commit conventionnel pour chacun. Puis rédige un unique corps de "
"PR inter-dépôts. Committe chaque dépôt avec son message ; laisse la PR en "
"brouillon à blanc. »_"

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:519 learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:668
msgid "Claude will:"
msgstr "Claude va :"

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:521
msgid "call **`changeset_repos_tool()`** → sees `kernel`, `hal`,"
msgstr "appeler **`changeset_repos_tool()`** → voit `kernel`, `hal`,"

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:522
msgid ""
"call **`repo_diff(\"kernel\")`** and **`repo_diff(\"hal\")`** → reads "
"exactly what changed,"
msgstr ""
"appeler **`repo_diff(\"kernel\")`** et **`repo_diff(\"hal\")`** → lit "
"exactement ce qui a changé,"

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:523
msgid ""
"write conventional-commit messages (e.g. `fix(kernel): guard against null "
"irq handler`),"
msgstr ""
"écrire des messages de commit conventionnels (ex. `fix(kernel): guard "
"against null irq handler`),"

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:524
msgid ""
"call **`write_commit(\"kernel\", …)`** and **`write_commit(\"hal\", …)`** — "
"each **path-guarded** to your workspace,"
msgstr ""
"appeler **`write_commit(\"kernel\", …)`** et **`write_commit(\"hal\", …)`** "
"— chacun **protégé par garde-chemin** vers ton espace de travail,"

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:526
msgid ""
"call **`draft_pr(\"kernel\", \"…\", \"…\")`** → returns a PR body **dry** "
"(nothing pushed)."
msgstr ""
"appeler **`draft_pr(\"kernel\", \"…\", \"…\")`** → renvoie un corps de PR "
"**à blanc** (rien n'est poussé)."

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:528
msgid ""
"You review the drafts, and when you're happy, run `haw change request` "
"yourself (or let Claude call `draft_pr(..., submit=True)`)."
msgstr ""
"Tu relis les brouillons, et quand tu es satisfait, tu lances `haw change "
"request` toi-même (ou tu laisses Claude appeler `draft_pr(..., "
"submit=True)`)."

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:533
msgid ""
"**Being honest about Level 1.** At this point, Claude Code already sees a "
"single repo's diff natively — you haven't given it a superpower yet, you've "
"just taught it to speak haw's protocol cleanly. The real power arrives at "
"**Level 2**: showing it an _entire_ changeset, spread across several repos, "
"in a single view."
msgstr ""
"**Soyons honnêtes à propos du Niveau 1.** À ce stade, Claude Code voit déjà "
"nativement le diff d'un unique dépôt — tu ne lui as pas encore donné de "
"super-pouvoir, tu lui as juste appris à parler proprement le protocole de "
"haw. La vraie puissance arrive au **Niveau 2** : lui montrer un changeset "
"_entier_, réparti sur plusieurs dépôts, dans une seule vue."

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:540
msgid ""
"So far we've mostly reinvented what Claude does for one repo for free. Keep "
"the faith: the next level is the part it _can't_ do on its own."
msgstr ""
"Jusqu'ici, on a surtout réinventé ce que Claude fait gratuitement pour un "
"seul dépôt. Garde la foi : le niveau suivant est la partie qu'il _ne peut "
"pas_ faire tout seul."

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:546
msgid ""
"_\"We built a whole plugin to do what Claude already did.\" This is fine — "
"Level 2 fixes it._"
msgstr ""
"_« On a construit tout un plugin pour faire ce que Claude faisait déjà. » "
"C'est très bien — le Niveau 2 corrige ça._"

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:550
msgid "**Your turn (Level 1)**"
msgstr "**À toi de jouer (Niveau 1)**"

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:552
msgid ""
"Scaffold your own: <code>haw plugins new commit-ai --lang python</code>, "
"then run the zero-dependency face with <code>haw commit-ai --format json</"
"code> and confirm you get a <code>haw.plugin.report/1</code> document."
msgstr ""
"Génère le tien : <code>haw plugins new commit-ai --lang python</code>, puis "
"lance la face sans dépendance avec <code>haw commit-ai --format json</code> "
"et confirme que tu obtiens un document <code>haw.plugin.report/1</code>."

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:553
msgid ""
"Drop the plugin on <code>PATH</code>, open <code>haw dash</code>, press "
"<code>7</code>, and select <code>commit-ai</code> — your "
"<code>haw.plugin.view/1</code> panel renders right in the cockpit."
msgstr ""
"Dépose le plugin sur le <code>PATH</code>, ouvre <code>haw dash</code>, "
"appuie sur <code>7</code>, et sélectionne <code>commit-ai</code> — ton "
"panneau <code>haw.plugin.view/1</code> s'affiche directement dans le cockpit."

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:554
msgid ""
"<code>pip install mcp</code>, register it with <code>claude mcp add …</"
"code>, and ask Claude to read one repo's diff and propose a commit — "
"<em>without</em> committing. Then let it call <code>write_commit</code>, and "
"watch the path-guard in action by asking it to commit a path outside the "
"workspace (it should refuse)."
msgstr ""
"<code>pip install mcp</code>, enregistre-le avec <code>claude mcp add …</"
"code>, et demande à Claude de lire le diff d'un dépôt et de proposer un "
"commit — <em>sans</em> committer. Puis laisse-le appeler <code>write_commit</"
"code>, et observe le garde-fou de chemin en action en lui demandant de "
"committer un chemin hors de l'espace de travail (il devrait refuser)."

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:560
msgid "Level 2 — the cross-repo power (changeset-wide)"
msgstr "Niveau 2 — la puissance inter-dépôts (à l'échelle du changeset)"

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:562
msgid ""
"Here's the pitch, sharp: **Claude alone can't see a fleet-wide changeset.** "
"It can read one repo's diff — but a haw changeset spans several repos at "
"once (`kernel`, `hal`, `app`…), and that combined story lives _between_ the "
"repos. A single-repo tool like lazygit can't show it either. haw knows the "
"whole changeset, so haw can hand Claude the whole picture."
msgstr ""
"Voici l'argument, tranchant : **Claude seul ne peut pas voir un changeset "
"couvrant toute la flotte.** Il peut lire le diff d'un dépôt — mais un "
"changeset haw s'étend sur plusieurs dépôts à la fois (`kernel`, `hal`, "
"`app`…), et cette histoire combinée vit _entre_ les dépôts. Un outil mono-"
"dépôt comme lazygit ne peut pas la montrer non plus. haw connaît tout le "
"changeset, donc haw peut tendre à Claude l'image complète."

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:567
msgid ""
"We add **two tools to the same plugin** — no new script, no new server. They "
"turn `haw-commit-ai` from \"a nice commit helper\" into \"the thing that "
"gives an LLM fleet-wide vision.\""
msgstr ""
"On ajoute **deux outils au même plugin** — pas de nouveau script, pas de "
"nouveau serveur. Ils transforment `haw-commit-ai` de « un sympathique "
"assistant de commit » en « la chose qui donne à un LLM une vision de toute "
"la flotte »."

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:571
msgid "11. Why cross-repo is the unique value"
msgstr "11. Pourquoi l'inter-dépôts est la valeur unique"

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:573
msgid ""
"Imagine you add one feature — say an `irq_mask` flag — and it has to land in "
"three repos at once: the `kernel` driver that owns the register, the `hal` "
"layer that threads it through, and the `app` that exposes it on the CLI. "
"Each repo's diff, read alone, is a fragment. The _meaning_ — \"these three "
"moves are one feature and must land together\" — only exists when you see "
"all three diffs side by side."
msgstr ""
"Imagine que tu ajoutes une fonctionnalité — disons un flag `irq_mask` — et "
"qu'elle doive atterrir dans trois dépôts à la fois : le pilote `kernel` qui "
"possède le registre, la couche `hal` qui le fait circuler, et l'`app` qui "
"l'expose sur la CLI. Le diff de chaque dépôt, lu seul, n'est qu'un fragment. "
"Le _sens_ — « ces trois mouvements ne sont qu'une seule fonctionnalité et "
"doivent atterrir ensemble » — n'existe que lorsque tu vois les trois diffs "
"côte à côte."

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:579
msgid ""
"Claude, on its own, reads one repo at a time. It can't see the fragments as "
"one story."
msgstr ""
"Claude, tout seul, lit un dépôt à la fois. Il ne peut pas voir les fragments "
"comme une seule histoire."

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:580
msgid "A single-repo tool sees one repo, full stop."
msgstr "Un outil mono-dépôt voit un seul dépôt, point final."

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:581
msgid ""
"**haw knows the changeset**, so it can concatenate every repo's diff into "
"one document and hand that to Claude. Now Claude writes **one** coherent PR "
"that narrates the whole feature."
msgstr ""
"**haw connaît le changeset**, donc il peut concaténer le diff de chaque "
"dépôt en un seul document et le tendre à Claude. Désormais, Claude écrit "
"**une** PR cohérente qui raconte toute la fonctionnalité."

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:584
msgid ""
"That combined view is the unique value. Everything in Level 2 exists to "
"deliver it."
msgstr ""
"Cette vue combinée est la valeur unique. Tout ce qui compose le Niveau 2 "
"existe pour la livrer."

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:586
msgid "12. Two cross-repo tools"
msgstr "12. Deux outils inter-dépôts"

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:588
msgid ""
"Drop these alongside the Level 1 tools (the shipped [`examples/plugins/haw-"
"commit-ai/haw-commit-ai`](https://github.com/Nastwinns/hawser/tree/main/"
"examples/plugins/haw-commit-ai) already has them). First, the helper that "
"builds the combined diff — it concatenates every repo's diff under a clear "
"`=== <repo> ===` header:"
msgstr ""
"Dépose-les à côté des outils du Niveau 1 (le fichier livré [`examples/"
"plugins/haw-commit-ai/haw-commit-ai`](https://github.com/Nastwinns/hawser/"
"tree/main/examples/plugins/haw-commit-ai) les possède déjà). D'abord, "
"l'utilitaire qui construit le diff combiné — il concatène le diff de chaque "
"dépôt sous un en-tête clair `=== <repo> ===` :"

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:595
msgid ""
"\"\"\"The COMBINED git diff across every repo of the current changeset.\"\"\""
msgstr ""
"\"\"\"Le diff git COMBINÉ à travers chaque dépôt du changeset courant.\"\"\""

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:598
msgid "\"no changeset and no dirty repos — nothing to diff.\""
msgstr "\"pas de changeset et pas de dépôts sales — rien à comparer.\""

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:600
msgid "# clear per-repo headers\n"
msgstr "# en-têtes clairs par dépôt\n"

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:602
msgid "\"(no changes)\""
msgstr "\"(aucun changement)\""

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:603
msgid "\"=== "
msgstr "\"=== "

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:603 learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:624
msgid "'?'"
msgstr "'?'"

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:603
msgid " ===\\n"
msgstr " ===\\n"

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:604
msgid "\"\\n\\n\""
msgstr "\"\\n\\n\""

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:604
msgid "# the whole story, top to bottom\n"
msgstr "# toute l'histoire, de haut en bas\n"

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:607
msgid ""
"This is the **killer function**: one call, and Claude sees `kernel`, `hal`, "
"and `app`'s diffs concatenated under `=== <repo> ===` headers — the fleet-"
"wide changeset as a single readable document."
msgstr ""
"C'est la **fonction phare** : un seul appel, et Claude voit les diffs de "
"`kernel`, `hal` et `app` concaténés sous des en-têtes `=== <repo> ===` — le "
"changeset couvrant toute la flotte comme un unique document lisible."

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:611
msgid ""
"Next, the helper that builds a single cross-repo PR skeleton — a combined-"
"summary slot plus one section per repo, which Claude then fills with prose:"
msgstr ""
"Ensuite, l'utilitaire qui construit un unique squelette de PR inter-dépôts — "
"un emplacement de résumé combiné plus une section par dépôt, que Claude "
"remplit ensuite avec de la prose :"

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:616
msgid ""
"\"\"\"ONE coherent cross-repo PR skeleton narrating every repo together."
"\"\"\""
msgstr ""
"\"\"\"UN squelette de PR inter-dépôts cohérent racontant tous les dépôts "
"ensemble.\"\"\""

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:618
msgid "\"## Combined summary\""
msgstr "\"## Résumé combiné\""

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:619
msgid ""
"\"<!-- one narrative covering all repos and why they move together -->\""
msgstr ""
"\"<!-- un récit couvrant tous les dépôts et pourquoi ils évoluent ensemble --"
">\""

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:620
msgid "\"## Per-repo changes\""
msgstr "\"## Changements par dépôt\""

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:623
msgid "\" ("
msgstr "\" ("

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:623
msgid " file(s), "
msgstr " fichier(s), "

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:623
msgid " line(s))\""
msgstr " ligne(s))\""

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:624
msgid "\"### "
msgstr "\"### "

#: learn/08-build-a-plugin-mcp.md:624
msgid "\"<!-- what changed here and why -->\""
msgstr "\"<!-- ce qui a changé ici et pourquoi -->\""

